ildare Borough (Parliament of Ireland constituency)|Kildare Borough]] in 1761, for which he chose to sit</ref>\n| <!-- party -->\n| rowspan=\"2\" style=\"background-color: {{/meta/color}}\" |\n| rowspan=\"2\" | [[James McManus (politician)|James McManus]] \n| rowspan=\"2\" | <!-- party -->\n|-\n| 1761\n| rowspan=\"3\" style=\"background-color: {{/meta/color}}\" |\n| rowspan=\"3\" | [[Robert Sandford (1722\u20131793)|Robert Sandford]] \n| rowspan=\"3\" | <!-- party -->\n|-\n| December 1761\n| style=\"background-color: {{/meta/color}}\" |\n| [[Richard Stearne Tighe]] \n| <!-- party -->\n|-\n| 1762\n| style=\"background-color: {{/meta/color}}\" |\n| [[William Smith (Irish politician)|William Smith]] \n| <!-- party -->\n|-\n| 1768\n| style=\"background-color: {{/meta/color}}\" |\n| [[John St Leger (Irish politician)|John St Leger]] \n| <!-- party -->\n| rowspan=\"2\" style=\"background-color: {{/meta/color}}\" |\n| rowspan=\"2\" | [[William de Burgh (MP)|William Burgh]] \n| rowspan=\"2\" | <!-- party -->\n|-\n| 1769\n| style=\"background-color: {{Irish Patriot Party/meta/color}}\" |\n| [[Walter Hussey Burgh]] \n| [[Irish Patriot Party|Patriot]]\n|-\n| 1776\n| style=\"background-color: {{/meta/color}}\" |\n| [[Thomas Burgh (1754\u20131832)|Thomas Burgh]] \n| <!-- party -->\n| rowspan=\"2\" style=\"background-color: {{/meta/color}}\" |\n| rowspan=\"2\" | [[Thomas Burgh (MP died 1810)|Thomas Burgh]] \n| rowspan=\"2\" | <!-- party -->\n|-\n| 1783\n| style=\"background-color: {{Irish Patriot Party/meta/color}}\" |\n| [[Lord Edward FitzGerald]] \n| [[Irish Patriot Party|Patriot]]\n|-\n| 1790\n| style=\"background-color: {{Irish Patriot Party/meta/color}}\" |\n| [[Lord Henry FitzGerald]] <ref group = \"note\">Also elected for [[Dublin City (Parliament of Ireland constituency)|Dublin City]] in 1790, for which he chose to sit</ref>\n| [[Irish Patriot Party|Patriot]]\n| rowspan=\"2\" style=\"background-color: {{/meta/color}}\" |\n| rowspan=\"2\" | [[Arthur Ormsby]] \n| rowspan=\"